SUMMARY:Swarthmore Summer Scholars Program (S3P) Poster Session
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Poster Session\\
 nThe Swarthmore Summer Scholar Program (S3P) invites the campus community 
 to visit our Annual Poster Session on Friday\, August 1st from 10am-11:30a
 m in Singer Atrium. This July\, the S3P Scholars have been learning about 
 how cells divide. For their culminating projects\, they are designing\, co
 nducting\, and analyzing their own experiments to examine the effects of c
 hemicals on cell division. Please drop in anytime between 10am and 11:30am
  to meet this amazing cohort of incoming first-year students and see what 
 they’ve discovered! We are excited to see you there!  The Annual Swarthm
 ore Summer Scholars Program Poster Session Celebrating the S3P Class of 20
 29 Friday\, August 1\, 10am-11:30am\, Singer Atrium  \\nDetails: https://
 swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D139274555
 0
LOCATION:Singer First Floor Commons
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1392745550
CATEGORIES:Poster Session
END:VEVENT
