SUMMARY:Peter van de Kamp Observatory Open House
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Physics and Astronomy']\\nCategory: Open House\
 \nThe Physics and Astronomy department hosts a telescope open house on the
  second Tuesday of each month at the Peter van de Kamp Observatory on the 
 roof of the Science Center. Directions are available at www.swarthmore.ed
 u/peter-van-de-kamp-observatory/directions. The open house hours are 8:00 
 p.m. to 9:00 p.m. during standard time and 9:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m. during 
 daylight savings time. The SC-1 exterior door under the breezeway will be 
 open 10 minutes before the start time. The rooftop access door will open a
 t the event start time. If the weather is bad\, the open house will be can
 celled by 5:00 p.m.\, and an announcement will be posted on the Physics an
 d Astronomy department website and the College calendar. Check https://ww
 w.swarthmore.edu/physics-astronomy on the day of the open house if the wea
 ther is questionable Open to the public. \\nDetails: https://swatcentral.
 swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1364584549
LOCATION:Science Center Peter Van de Kamp Observatory\, Science Center Obse
 rvatory Computer Room
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1364584549
CATEGORIES:Open House
END:VEVENT
